  "prompt": "How do I get over a crush on my guy best friend?",
  "response": "Getting over a crush on your guy best friend can be challenging, especially since your friendship adds another layer of complexity. Here are some steps to help you work through your feelings:\n\n1. **Acknowledge Your Feelings:** Accept that it's normal to have these feelings. Understand that they are a part of your emotional landscape but do not define your friendship or self-worth.\n\n2. **Reflect on Why You Like Him:** Consider what qualities you admire in him and whether these are truly romantic in nature or rooted in admiration and appreciation as a friend.\n\n3. **Focus on Friendship:** Shift your focus back to the platonic aspects of your relationship. Remind yourself of the value of your friendship and why you cherish it.\n\n4. **Create Emotional Distance:** It may be helpful to take a step back and give yourself some space to process your emotions. This could mean spending a little less time together or finding other friends to hang out with more.\n\n5. **Engage in New Activities:** Distract yourself by trying new hobbies or activities, which can also help you meet new people and potentially develop new interests.\n\n6. **Talk to Someone:** Confide in a trusted friend or therapist who can provide perspective and support as you navigate your feelings.\n\n7. **Set Boundaries:** Establish clear boundaries for yourself to avoid situations that might intensify your feelings.\n\n8. **Focus on Self-Improvement:** Use this time to focus on personal growth, whether it\u2019s through learning new skills, exercising, or pursuing goals that you are passionate about.\n\n9. **Consider the Impact of Acting on Your Feelings:** If you\u2019re still considering this option, weigh the pros and cons, and think about how it might affect your friendship and personal comfort.\n\n10. **Time and Patience:** Recognize that moving on takes time. Be patient with yourself and understand that it's a gradual process.\n\nRemember, it's important to prioritize your emotional well-being and maintain relationships that are healthy and supportive for you.",
